36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.460" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 460</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.9.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 9, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.12.1" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 12, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.3.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 3, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.292" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 292</bibl>. Ff <emph>yond,</emph> Qq <cit><quote>yon:</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.3.53" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 3, 53</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 26</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.4.29" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.220" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 5, 220</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 18</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 18</bibl> In <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 3, 93</bibl> O. Edd. <emph>y. generation,</emph> M. Edd. <emph>the under generation.</emph><lb />2) adv. there: <cit><quote>say what thou seest y.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.409" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 409</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>y. 's that same knave,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 3.5.85" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 5, 85</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>y., methinks, he is,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.91" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 91</bibl></cit> (Qq <emph>yon methinks he stands</emph>). <cit><quote>is not y. Diomed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 5, 13</bibl></cit> (Ff <emph>young</emph>). <cit><quote>by all Diana's waiting-women y.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 5.2.91" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 91</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>what torch is y.</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.125" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 125</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 2, 28</bibl> (Qq <emph>yonder</emph>).
